Data.desc: As astronauts discover the first evidence of extra-terrestrial life on Mars, they begin realising that the life form is extremely intelligent and hostile.

Data.title: Apartment 1303 (2012)
Data.desc: Janet moves into apartment 1303 to escape from her alcoholic mother. Things take a dark turn when Janet's body is found and her sister Lara decides to investigate her sister's alleged suicide.

Data.title: Maze Runner: The Scorch Trials (2015)
Data.desc: Upon escaping the maze, Thomas and his friends are shifted to a facility meant to home the 'immunes'. When they realize its intent, they escape, only to face the scorching heat in a lifeless world.

Data.title: Children of Men (2006)
Data.desc: In 2027, 18 years of human infertility have left society on the verge of extinction. When one woman miraculously gets pregnant, Theo, a bureaucrat, must transport her to safety.

Data.title: The Sixth Sense (1999)
Data.desc: Malcolm Crowe, a child psychologist, starts treating a young boy who acts as a medium of communication between the former and a slew of unhappy spirits.

Data.title: A-X-L (2018)
Data.desc: Miles befriends A-X-L, a robotic dog, when he manages to activate its owner-pairing technology. However, Miles's life takes an unusual turn when A-X-L's creators come searching for it.

Data.title: Maze Runner: The Death Cure (2018)
Data.desc: When a deadly disease called The Flare breaks out, Thomas and his group of escaped Gladers break in to the Last City to find the cure and save their friends.

Data.title: Seraphim Falls (2007)
Data.desc: At the end of the American Civil War, a colonel puts together a team to hunt down a man against whom he holds a grudge.

Data.title: Godzilla: King of the Monsters (2019)
Data.desc: Members of the crypto-zoological agency Monarch face off against a battery of god-sized monsters, including the mighty Godzilla, who collides with Mothra, Rodan, and his ultimate nemesis, the three-headed King Ghidorah. When these ancient super-species-thought to be mere myths-rise again, they all vie for supremacy, leaving humanity's very existence hanging in the balance.

Data.title: The Hunger Games: Mockingjay - Part 2 (2015)
Data.desc: After realising that she is no longer fighting only for survival, Katniss sets out on a mission to assassinate President Snow and liberate the people of Panem with help from her friends.

Data.title: Star Trek (2009)
Data.desc: James Kirk, a brash young man, and Spock, an alien with human and Vulcan blood, join the crew of the USS Enterprise to combat Nero, a member of the Romulan race who wants to destroy multiple planets.

Data.title: Avengers: Endgame (2019)
Data.desc: Adrift in space with no food or water, Tony Stark sends a message to Pepper Potts as his oxygen supply starts to dwindle. Meanwhile, the remaining Avengers -- Thor, Black Widow, Captain America and Bruce Banner -- must figure out a way to bring back their vanquished allies for an epic showdown with Thanos -- the evil demigod who decimated the planet and the universe.

Data.title: Mad Max 2: The Road Warrior (1981)
Data.desc: In the post-apocalyptic Australian wasteland, a cynical drifter agrees to help a small, gasoline rich community escape a horde of bandits.

Data.title: Lilo & Stitch 2: Stitch Has a Glitch (2005)
Data.desc: As Stitch helps his friend to prepare for the annual Hula festival, things go haywire, and now it's up to Stitch and his friends to get things organized.

Data.title: The Lion King (2019)
Data.desc: Simba idolizes his father, King Mufasa, and takes to heart his own royal destiny on the plains of Africa. But not everyone in the kingdom celebrates the new cub's arrival. Scar, Mufasa's brother -- and former heir to the throne -- has plans of his own. The battle for Pride Rock is soon ravaged with betrayal, tragedy and drama, ultimately resulting in Simba's exile. Now, with help from a curious pair of newfound friends, Simba must figure out how to grow up and take back what is rightfully his.

Data.title: Gravity (2013)
Data.desc: Dr Ryan Stone, an engineer on her first time on a space mission, and Matt Kowalski, an astronaut on his final expedition, have to survive in space after they are hit by debris while spacewalking.

Data.title: Shakespeare in Love (1998)
Data.desc: William Shakespeare is looking for a muse to help with his writing. When he meets Viola, who loves the theatre, she plays the part perfectly. However, she is promised to Lord Wessex in marriage.

Data.title: The Rescuers (1977)
Data.desc: Bernard (Bob Newhart) and Miss Bianca (Eva Gabor), two New York City mice, are members of the Rescue Aid Society, an international team that operates beneath the United Nations and comes to the aid of those in need. After receiving word that Penny (Michelle Stacy), a young orphan, has been abducted by Madame Medusa (Geraldine Page), an evil woman seeking a precious diamond, the two set out to bring her back home, with help from other animal friends.

Data.title: Men in Black: International (2019)
Data.desc: The Men in Black have expanded to cover the globe but so have the villains of the universe. To keep everyone safe, decorated Agent H and determined rookie M join forces -- an unlikely pairing that just might work. When aliens that can take the form of any human arrive on Earth, H and M embark on a globe-trotting adventure to save the agency -- and ultimately the world -- from their mischievous plans.

Data.title: Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows - Part 1 (2010)
Data.desc: Without the guidance and protection of their professors, Harry (Daniel Radcliffe), Ron (Rupert Grint) and Hermione (Emma Watson) begin a mission to destroy the Horcruxes, the sources of Voldemort's immortality. Though they must rely on one another more than ever, dark forces threaten to tear them apart. Voldemort's Death Eaters have seized control of the Ministry of Magic and Hogwarts, and they are searching for Harry -- even as he and his friends prepare for the ultimate showdown.

Data.title: Shrek Forever After (2010)
Data.desc: Shrek finds himself burdened and in the midst of a mid-life crisis. Rumpelstiltskin convinces him to let him cast him in a world where he sets the rules.

Data.title: Pet Sematary (2019)
Data.desc: Dr. Louis Creed and his wife, Rachel, relocate from Boston to rural Maine with their two young children. The couple soon discover a mysterious burial ground hidden deep in the woods near their new home. When tragedy strikes, Louis turns to his neighbour Jud Crandall, setting off a perilous chain reaction that unleashes an unspeakable evil with horrific consequences.

Data.title: Point Blank (2019)
Data.desc: Pitted against rival gangs and corrupt cops, an ER nurse and a career criminal must work together to survive the fight of their lives.

Data.title: Shaft (2019)
Data.desc: John Shaft Jr. may be an FBI cyber security expert, but to uncover the truth behind his best friend's untimely death, he needs an education that only his dad can provide. Absent throughout his childhood, the legendary John Shaft agrees to help his son navigate the heroin-infested underbelly of Harlem, N.Y. Besides, the locked and loaded Shaft has his own score to settle -- both professional and personal.

Data.title: Teen Spirit (2018)
Data.desc: A shy teenager dreams of escaping her small town and pursuing her passion to sing. With the help of an unlikely mentor, she enters a local singing competition that will test her integrity, talent and ambition.

Data.title: Bleeding Steel (2017)
Data.desc: As special agent Lin Dong tries to arrest a mecha-enhanced criminal, he discovers that his missing daughter is a part of a dangerous biochemistry experiment.

Data.title: It (2017)
Data.desc: Seven helpless and bullied children are forced to face their worst nightmares when Pennywise, a shape-shifting clown, reappears. The clown lives in the sewers and targets small innocent children.

Data.title: Mississippi River Sharks (2017)
Data.desc: A school of sharks attacks the participants of a fishing tournament in the Mississippi River and it is down to the locals to stop the predators and save the entire town.

Data.title: Masterminds (2016)
Data.desc: Philip, a security guard, plans a bank heist along with three other friends. When the FBI begins investigating the case, the four accused succumb to pressure and turn on each other.

Data.title: Chappie (2015)
Data.desc: Chappie, one of the police robots, is stolen by criminals who treat it like their own child. With new programming, it becomes the first robot with the ability to feel and think for itself.

Data.title: Fantastic Four (2015)
Data.desc: Four youngsters gain unique superpowers after being teleported to an alternate universe. They must unite and use their powers to fight against a computer mechanic, who transforms into an evil doctor.

Data.title: Mission: Impossible - Rogue Nation (2015)
Data.desc: With the IMF disbanded and the CIA hunting him, Ethan and his team race against time to prove the existence of the Syndicate, a highly-skilled terror organisation, before they plan their next attack.

Data.title: Stormageddon (2015
Data.desc: A rogue software system seizes control of the US defence network's computers, gaining the ability to manipulate the weather and threaten devastation.

Data.title: Terminator Genisys (2015)
Data.desc: John sends Kyle to the year 1984 to protect his mother Sarah from being killed. When the timeline is altered, Kyle asks her to travel to the year 2017 to stop an AI system that wants to wipe mankind.

Data.title: The Transporter Refueled (2015)
Data.desc: Frank Martin, a former special-ops mercenary and transporter, is hired by Anna and her accomplices to fulfil a contract. But soon he must join forces with them to bring down a Russian crimelord.

Data.title: Fury (2014)
Data.desc: Wardaddy, along with a five-man crew, embarks on a mission that puts their lives in danger. They realise that the odds are against them, but still decide to attack the Nazi army.

Data.title: The Prince (2014)
Data.desc: A retired assassin is drawn back into the life he gave up when his daughter is kidnapped. To rescue her, he must confront his former rival.

Data.title: Empire Of The Apes (2017)
Data.desc: Three escaped female convicts must fight for their lives after they crash on a planet dominated by a race of intelligent, warlike apes.

Data.title: Urban Cannibal Massacre (2013)
Data.desc: The lives of two cannibalistic people who prey on the homeless are threatened when their daughter becomes a vegan and falls in love with one of their potential victims.

Data.title: The Man with the Iron Fists (2012)
Data.desc: Gold Lion, chief of a jungle clan, is betrayed and murdered by his lieutenants Silver and Bronze Lion when he is asked to look after a large amount of gold. His son Zen Yi swears revenge.

Data.title: Ghost Rider: Spirit of Vengeance (2011)
Data.desc: A French priest seeks the Ghost Rider's help to save a young boy from the devil. In exchange, he offers to return Johnny's soul, but in order to succeed Johnny must first confront his own demons.

Data.title: The Chronicles of Narnia: The Voyage of the Dawn Treader (2010)
Data.desc: Siblings Edmund and Lucy, along with their cousin Eustace, face challenges after teaming up with the new king of Narnia, Caspian, to save the realm from a dismal force and rescue the seven lost lords.

Data.title: Crank: High Voltage (2009)
Data.desc: Chinese medics harvest Chev's heart and replace it with an artificial one. He later learns that his real heart is with Johnny and races to find him before the battery in his artificial heart runs out.

Data.title: Fast & Furious (2009)
Data.desc: Dominic Toretto, a street racer and ex-convict, teams up with FBI agent Brian O'Connor to take on a heroin importer in LA and avenge his girlfriend's murder.

Data.title: Fighting (2009)
Data.desc: Shawn tries to make a living by selling replicas on the streets of New York. He starts making a small fortune when a man introduces him to the world of underground street fighting.

Data.title: Bangkok Dangerous (2008)
Data.desc: Joe, a hit man, arrives in Bangkok, hires Kong as his errand boy and begins work. He soon realises that he has begun to break his four rules of being a hit man, without which he is bound to fall prey.

Data.title: Doomsday (2008)
Data.desc: Eden Sinclair and her team of specialists are sent to a zombie-ravaged Scotland to retrieve a cure for a virus known as Reaper which is threatening to wipe away humanity.

Data.title: In Bruges (2008)
Data.desc: Ray and Ken, two hitmen, get stuck in Bruges, Belgium, after an unsuccessful mission. The situation becomes complicated when their boss asks Ken to kill Ray.

Data.title: The Chronicles of Narnia: Prince Caspian (2008)
Data.desc: Four children set out to help Prince Caspian who struggles to win back his throne from King Miraz, his evil uncle.

Data.title: Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer (2007)
Data.desc: A group of superheroes battles an intergalactic herald, Silver Surfer, who comes to the Earth in order to serve his master, Galactus. Galactus thrives for planets and the Earth is his next target.

Data.title: Ghost Rider (2007)
Data.desc: Stunt motorcyclist Johnny Blaze decides to give up his soul to become the Ghost Rider and fight against Blackheart, the son of Mephistopheles, the devil himself.

Data.title: Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix (2007)
Data.desc: Harry Potter and Dumbledore's warning about the return of Lord Voldemort is not heeded by the wizard authorities who, in turn, look to undermine Dumbledore's authority at Hogwarts and discredit Harry.

Data.title: The Fast and the Furious: Tokyo Drift (2006)
Data.desc: In order to avoid jail time, an errant car racer is sent to live with his father in Tokyo. When he loses a drift race to the underworld connected Drift King, he has to find a way to pay his debt.

Data.title: The Chronicles of Narnia: The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe (2005)
Data.desc: While playing, Lucy and her siblings find a wardrobe that lands them in a mystical place called Narnia. Here they realise that it was fated and they must now unite with Aslan to defeat an evil queen.

Data.title: Underworld (2003)
Data.desc: Selene, a vampire orphaned due to a deadly werewolf attack, works for a vampire clan as a trained murderer. She battles to save Michael, a skilled human doctor, from the machinations of werewolves.

Data.title: The Fast and the Furious (2001)
Data.desc: Los Angeles police officer Brian O'Conner must decide where his loyalty really lies when he becomes enamored with the street racing world he has been sent undercover to destroy.

Data.title: Jumanji (1995)
Data.desc: When two kids find and play a magical board game, they release a man trapped for decades in it and a host of dangers that can only be stopped by finishing the game.

Data.title: The Empire Strikes Back (1980)
Data.desc: Darth Vader is adamant about turning Luke Skywalker to the dark side. Master Yoda trains Luke to become a Jedi Knight while his friends try to fend off the Imperial fleet.

Data.title: Terminator 2: Judgment Day (1991)
Data.desc: A terminator is set on a mission to kill Sarah's son, John Connor. However, a cyborg, who once was after the life of Sarah, has been assigned to protect him.

Data.title: The Matrix (1999)
Data.desc: Thomas Anderson, a computer programmer, is led to fight an underground war against powerful computers who have constructed his entire reality with a system called the Matrix.

Data.title: Underworld: Awakening (2012)
Data.desc: Selene, a vampire warrior, finds out that the humans have decided to eradicate her clan and leads a battle, along with another vampire and a young girl, against them.

Data.title: Snitch (2013)
Data.desc: John Matthews' estranged son Jason is wrongly arrested for drug trafficking. John enters the narcotics underworld to arrest its kingpins in order to save his son from imprisonment in return.

Data.title: War of the Worlds (2005)
Data.desc: Ray Ferrier, a dockworker, and his children are all set to spend a weekend together. But an alien tripod descends on Earth, threatening to wipe out humanity.

Data.title: John Wick: Chapter 2 (2017)
Data.desc: Renowned assassin John Wick sets out for Rome to duel with some of the deadliest killers after he learns that he is in danger.

Data.title: Spider-Man 3 (2007)
Data.desc: Peter Parker becomes one with a symbiotic alien that bolsters his Spider-Man avatar and affects his psyche. He also has to deal with Sandman and maintain a fragmented relationship with Mary Jane.

Data.title: Pirates of the Caribbean: On Stranger Tides (2011)
Data.desc: Captain Jack Sparrow sets sail in search of the legendary fountain of youth. His mission puts him up against a mysterious woman from his past, old enemy Barbossa and the feared pirate, Blackbeard.

Data.title: Pirates of the Caribbean: The Curse of the Black Pearl (2003)
Data.desc: A blacksmith joins forces with Captain Jack Sparrow, a pirate, in a bid to free the love of his life from Jack's associates, who kidnapped her suspecting she has the medallion.

Data.title: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Man's Chest (2006)
Data.desc: Captain Jack Sparrow seeks the heart of Davy Jones, a mythical pirate, in order to avoid being enslaved to him. However, others, including his friends Will and Elizabeth, want it for their own ends.

Data.title: Shutter Island (2010)
Data.desc: Teddy Daniels and Chuck Aule, two US marshals, are sent to an asylum on a remote island in order to investigate the disappearance of a patient, but Teddy uncovers a shocking truth about the place.

Data.title: Police Story (2013)
Data.desc: While visiting his estranged daughter (Jing Tian) at a nightclub, a police captain (Jackie Chan) must spring into action when an elaborate kidnapping plan unravels right before his eyes.

Data.title: Crank (2006)
Data.desc: Chev, an assassin-for-hire, is injected with a serum that requires him to always keep his adrenaline levels high in order to survive.

Data.title: Transporter 2 (2005)
Data.desc: Frank Martin, a transporter, is accused of kidnapping a young boy. He then sets out to rescue the boy and prevent the kidnappers from realising their evil plans.

Data.title: Beauty and the Beast (2017)
Data.desc: Belle, a village girl, embarks on a journey to save her father from a creature that has locked him in his dungeon. Eventually, she learns that the creature is an enchanted prince who has been cursed.

Data.title: The Hobbit: The Desolation of Smaug (2013)
Data.desc: Bilbo Baggins and his companions escape great dangers and continue their journey to Lake-town. They finally arrive to the Lonely Mountain only to encounter Smaug, the most fearsome dragon.

Data.title: The Transporter (2002)
Data.desc: An ex-soldier turned mercenary 'transporter' moves goods, human or otherwise, from one place to another. Complications arise when a job goes astray and he has to save the life of his female cargo.

Data.title: The Hobbit: The Battle of the Five Armies (2014)
Data.desc: Bilbo fights against a number of enemies to save the life of his Dwarf friends and protects the Lonely Mountain after a conflict arises.

Data.title: Iron Man 3 (2013)
Data.desc: Tony Stark encounters a formidable foe called the Mandarin. After failing to defeat his enemy, he embarks on a journey with relentless consequences and a suit that ceases to exist.

Data.title: Mission Impossible: Ghost Protocol (2011)
Data.desc: When the IMF is wrongly accused of bombing the Kremlin, Ethan and his team race against time to find the culprits and clear the reputation of their organisation.

Data.title: Alien: Covenant (2017)
Data.desc: The crew abroad Covenant, a colonization ship, bound for Origae-6, a remote planet, receives a radio transmission from a habitable planet. There, they uncover a malicious threat and strive to escape.

Data.title: Dumbo (2019)
Data.desc: Struggling circus owner Max Medici enlists a former star and his two children to care for Dumbo, a baby elephant born with oversized ears. When the family discovers that the animal can fly, it soon becomes the main attraction -- bringing in huge audiences and revitalizing the run-down circus. The elephant's magical ability also draws the attention of V.A. Vandevere, an entrepreneur who wants to showcase Dumbo in his latest, larger-than-life entertainment venture.

Data.title: Girls Trip (2017)
Data.desc: When Ryan is invited to speak at the annual Essence Festival, she sees it as a chance to reconnect with her best friends Sasha, Lisa and Dina, and the girls set out on a trip to New Orleans.

Data.title: The Hunger Games: Mockingjay - Part 1 (2014)
Data.desc: Although the Games no longer exist, Katniss Everdeen, Gale, Finnick and Beetee join forces to save Peeta and the world.

Data.title: Godzilla (2014)
Data.desc: Ford and his father Joe find evidence pointing to the existence of giant creatures. When the creatures, classified as MUTO, surface, Godzilla, an ancient behemoth, rises to fight them.

Data.title: Anchorman 2: The Legend Continues (2013)
Data.desc: A celebrated news anchor from San Diego, post getting fired by his boss, is hired by New York's first 24-hour news channel where he takes the channel by storm through his new style of news coverage.

Data.title: Big Bad Bugs (2012)
Data.desc: After a convoy of American soldiers disappear on a routine mission, a special ops team is chosen and deployed to the area they were last located in an effort to find and rescue them. The special ops team soon encounter an army of gigantic scorpions, spiders and snakes that have come to Earth from another dimension.

Data.title: She's Out of My League (2010)
Data.desc: Kirk, a TSA agent, works at an airport. Things become interesting for him after he encounters Molly, a gorgeous woman at the airport. In a turn of events, they fall in love with each other.

Data.title: Revolutionary Road (2008)
Data.desc: Frank and April are an ideal couple who live with their two children in the suburbs of Connecticut. However, issues evolve in their marriage, and April decides to move to Paris.

Data.title: American Pie Presents: Beta House (2007)
Data.desc: Erik and Cooze become a part of the Beta House fraternity led by the famous Dwight. However, things take a turn when a gang of geeks decides to shut down the Beta House.

Data.title: Into The Wild (2007)
Data.desc: Christopher McCandless, a young graduate, decides to renounce all his possessions and hitchhike across America. During his journey, he encounters several situations which change him as a person.

Data.title: Fantastic Four (2005)
Data.desc: Four astronauts gain extraordinary powers like invisibility and stretchability after being hit by cosmic radiation. Now, their biggest challenge is Victor Von Doom, an evil doctor.

Data.title: How The Grinch Stole Christmas (2000)
Data.desc: Grinch lives in solitude just outside Whoville. He hates the townsfolk and despises Christmas. Cindy Lou, a six-year-old girl who believes in the spirit of the festival, sets out to reform him.

Data.title: Godzilla (1998)
Data.desc: An immense lizard, radioactively mutated, descends upon New York. Now it is up to the US Army and a team of dedicated investigators to unravel the mystery behind the creature before it is too late.

Data.title: The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring (2001)
Data.desc: A young hobbit, Frodo, who has found the One Ring that belongs to the Dark Lord Sauron, begins his journey with eight companions to Mount Doom, the only place where it can be destroyed.

Data.title: The Dark Knight (2008)
Data.desc: With the help of allies Lt. Jim Gordon (Gary Oldman) and DA Harvey Dent (Aaron Eckhart), Batman (Christian Bale) has been able to keep a tight lid on crime in Gotham City. But when a vile young criminal calling himself the Joker (Heath Ledger) suddenly throws the town into chaos, the caped Crusader begins to tread a fine line between heroism and vigilantism.

Data.title: Krampus (2015)
Data.desc: Frustrated by the constant quarrel between the members of his dysfunctional family, Max loses interest to celebrate Christmas, awakening Krampus, a demon who will punish his entire family.

Data.title: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales (2017)
Data.desc: Captain Jack Sparrow goes in search of the Trident of Poseidon in order to control the seas. Little does he know that his former rival, Captain Salazar, is waiting to avenge his defeat.

Data.title: Terminator 3: Rise of the Machines (2003)
Data.desc: John Connor, a cybernetic soldier, travels back in time in order to execute his mission of protecting a drifter and his wife, Kate Brewster, from a robotic attack.

Data.title: Pok√©mon Detective Pikachu (2019)
Data.desc: Ace detective Harry Goodman goes mysteriously missing, prompting his 21-year-old son, Tim, to find out what happened. Aiding in the investigation is Harry's former Pok√©mon partner, wise-cracking, adorable super-sleuth Detective Pikachu. Finding that they are uniquely equipped to work together, as Tim is the only human who can talk with Pikachu, they join forces to unravel the tangled mystery.

Data.title: Captain Marvel (2019)
Data.desc: Captain Marvel is an extraterrestrial Kree warrior who finds herself caught in the middle of an intergalactic battle between her people and the Skrulls. Living on Earth in 1995, she keeps having recurring memories of another life as U.S. Air Force pilot Carol Danvers. With help from Nick Fury, Captain Marvel tries to uncover the secrets of her past while harnessing her special superpowers to end the war with the evil Skrulls.

Data.title: Poltergeist (2015)
Data.desc: The Bowens must save their youngest daughter after she is taken captive by one of the evil spirits in their home.

Data.title: Chopsticks (2019)
Data.desc: A gifted but insecure woman has a transformational experience when she asks a con man to help recover her stolen car.

Data.title: Chestnut: Hero of Central Park (2004)
Data.desc: Two orphans smuggle their four-legged friend to their new home with adoptive parents. Initially, they are successful in hiding it from everyone. But, the growing puppy brings new challenges each day.

Data.title: Jim Button and Luke the Engine Driver (2018)
Data.desc: An orphan boy in search of his origin. A young princess held prisoner in deadly Dragon City. Jim and his friend Luke discovering mysterious lands on the quest of a lifetime.

Data.title: Smokin' Aces (2007)
Data.desc: A shifty magician decides to squeal on his own mob. But, before he heads off for protective custody, he decides to go to a casino for one last good time, drawing a crowd of assassins.

Data.title: The Matrix Revolutions (2003)
Data.desc: Neo, humanity's only hope of stopping the war and saving Zion, attempts to broker peace between the machines and humans. However, he must first confront his arch nemesis, the rogue agent Smith.

Data.title: The Unborn (2009)
Data.desc: When Casey believes that she is being haunted by the spirit of her twin brother who died in her mother's womb, she enlists the help of a rabbi to get rid of him.

Data.title: Alpha (2018)
Data.desc: Keda, the son of a tribe chief, tries to survive alone in the wilderness after his tribe leaves him. Incidentally, he finds himself in the company of an injured wolf abandoned by its pack.

Data.title: The Conjuring (2013)
Data.desc: Rod and Carolyn find their pet dog dead under mysterious circumstances and experience a spirit that harms their daughter Andrea. They finally call investigators who can help them get out of the mess.

Data.title: Bruce Almighty (2003)
Data.desc: A furious TV reporter demands an explanation from God for the injustice done to him. The Almighty gives him the power to run the world for a while, to teach him how difficult it is.

Data.title: Kingsman: The Secret Service (2015)
Data.desc: Gary 'Eggsy' Unwin faces several challenges when he gets recruited as a secret agent in a secret spy organisation in order to look for Richmond Valentine, an eco-terrorist.

Data.title: Falcon Rising (2014)
Data.desc: A former Marine (Michael Jai White) travels to Brazil to hunt down the brutal Japanese mobsters who attacked his sister and left her for dead.

Data.title: Rampage (2018)
Data.desc: Primatologist Davis Okoye teams up with a geneticist, Dr. Kate Caldwell, and an albino gorilla, George, to prevent three giant mutated animals from wreaking havoc in Chicago.

Data.title: Shazam! (2019)
Data.desc: We all have a superhero inside of us -- it just takes a bit of magic to bring it out. In 14-year-old Billy Batson's case, all he needs to do is shout out one word to transform into the adult superhero Shazam. Still a kid at heart, Shazam revels in the new version of himself by doing what any other teen would do -- have fun while testing out his newfound powers. But he'll need to master them quickly before the evil Dr. Thaddeus Sivana can get his hands on Shazam's magical abilities.

Data.title: Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows (2011)
Data.desc: With the help of his elder brother, Sherlock Holmes along with his associate, Dr Watson, ventures out on a mission to thwart the devious designs of their arch-rival, Professor Moriarty.

Data.title: Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom (1984)
Data.desc: Indiana Jones, a legendary archaeologist, finds himself in India, where a bunch of poor villagers reach out to him to track down an ancient stone that has been stolen by an evil priest.

Data.title: Iron Man 2 (2010)
Data.desc: Tony Stark is under pressure from various sources, including the government, to share his technology with the world. He must find a way to fight them while also tackling his other enemies.

Data.title: Now You See Me (2013)
Data.desc: Four street magicians, Daniel, Merritt, Henley and Jack ransack a huge amount of money belonging to insurance baron Arthur Tressler while being chased by FBI agent Dylan and Interpol agent Alma.

Data.title: Transformers (2007)
Data.desc: The noble Autobots and devious Decepticons, two intergalactic races of robots, crash-land on Earth. They battle for the AllSpark, the ultimate power source, whose location is held by Sam.

Data.title: Avengers: Age of Ultron (2015)
Data.desc: Tony Stark builds an artificial intelligence system named Ultron with the help of Bruce Banner. When the sentient Ultron makes plans to wipe out the human race, the Avengers set out to stop him.

Data.title: Fatal Contact (2006)
Data.desc: A man and his fight coach are best friends. His coach has taught him some great techniques that he plans to use for an underground tournament where he competes against the best fighters of the world.

Data.title: Duplex (2003)
Data.desc: A young couple moves into their new home. They do not expect the elderly lady living upstairs to be an issue, until her annoying habits forces them to use desperate measures.

Data.title: Don't Breathe (2016)
Data.desc: A troika of robbers barges into the house of a visually-impaired veteran after hearing that he has won prize money. Soon, they realise, much to their horror, that the old man is not that helpless.

Data.title: Charlie and the Chocolate Factory (2005)
Data.desc: Charlie, a young boy from an impoverished family, and four other kids win a tour of an amazing chocolate factory run by an imaginative chocolatier, Willy Wonka, and his staff of Oompa-Loompas.

Data.title: Spider-Man: Homecoming (2017)
Data.desc: Peter Parker tries to stop Adrian 'The Vulture' Toomes from selling weapons made with advanced Chitauri technology while trying to balance his life as an ordinary high school student.

Data.title: The Terminator (1984)
Data.desc: A cyborg assassin is sent back in time to kill Sarah, a waitress, in a bid to stop her son who will wage a long war against his enemy in the future unless the course of history is altered.

Data.title: Superman II (1980)
Data.desc: Superman decides to give up his superpowers for the sake of his true love, Lois Lane. At the same time, three criminals from his home planet of Krypton land on Earth and try to conquer the world.

Data.title: Against The Wild 2: Survive The Serengeti (2016)
Data.desc: Two kids and their dog have to survive in the African bush after their plane crashes.

Data.title: Outpost: Black Sun (2014)
Data.desc: A NATO task force tracks a Nazi war criminal and stumbles upon an army of walking dead Nazi soldiers killing their way across Europe.

Data.title: Push (2009)
Data.desc: Two young Americans with special abilities must race to find a girl in Hong Kong before a shadowy government organisation called Division does.

Data.title: Operation Red Sea (2018)
Data.desc: A Chinese special forces unit must rescue their fellow citizens in the country of Yewaire on the Arabian Peninsula amidst violent coup and threats from a terrorist group.

Data.title: About Time (2013)
Data.desc: Like all the men in his family, Tim Lake possesses the power to travel in time. With the advice of his father, he uses his special ability to pursue his romantic interest, Mary.

Data.title: The World's End (2013)
Data.desc: In an attempt to fulfil their epic pub crawl left incomplete 20 years ago, five friends return to their hometown. However, they are inadvertently burdened with the task of saving mankind.

Data.title: Terrordactyl (2016)
Data.desc: When ancient flying reptiles attack Los Angeles, it's up to two working-class friends, the unlikeliest of heroes, to save the day.

Data.title: The Ring Two (2005)
Data.desc: After the ordeal with Samara, Rachel and Aiden move to a rural town. Soon Rachel learns about the death of a girl in a similar fashion and she must dig into Samara's past even further.

Data.title: The Immigrant (2013)
Data.desc: After her sister is quarantined at Ellis Island, a Polish nurse (Marion Cotillard) is forced into prostitution by a theater manager (Joaquin Phoenix) who moonlights as a pimp.

Data.title: Superman (1978)
Data.desc: Scientist Jor-El rockets his infant son, Kal-El, to safety on Earth. Kal is raised as Clark Kent and develops unusual abilities and powers to become Superman who fights for truth and justice.

Data.title: Rise of the Planet of the Apes (2011)
Data.desc: Caesar, a chimpanzee, has been with Will ever since he was little. Will's new drug empowers Caesar to think and react like humans. When he finds himself subjected to injustice, he decides to revolt.

Data.title: Titanic (1997)
Data.desc: Seventeen-year-old Rose hails from an aristocratic family and is set to be married. When she boards the Titanic, she meets Jack Dawson, an artist, and falls in love with him.

Data.title: Thor: Ragnarok (2017)
Data.desc: Deprived of his mighty hammer Mjolnir, Thor must escape the other side of the universe to save his home, Asgard, from Hela, the goddess of death.

Data.title: Alita: Battle Angel (2019)
Data.desc: Set several centuries in the future, the abandoned Alita is found in the scrapyard of Iron City by Ido, a compassionate cyber-doctor who takes the unconscious cyborg Alita to his clinic. When Alita awakens, she has no memory of who she is, nor does she have any recognition of the world she finds herself in. As Alita learns to navigate her new life and the treacherous streets of Iron City, Ido tries to shield her from her mysterious past.

Data.title: The Little Hours (2017)
Data.desc: Medieval nuns Alessandra, Fernanda, and Ginevra lead a simple life in their convent. Their days are spent chafing at monastic routine, spying on one another, and berating the estate's day labourer. After a particularly vicious insult session drives the peasant away, Father Tommasso brings on newly hired hand Massetto, a virile young servant forced into hiding by his angry lord. Introduced to the sisters as a deaf-mute to discourage temptation, Massetto struggles to maintain his cover.

Data.title: Iraivi (2016)
Data.desc: Three men who are financially struggling get involved in criminal activities to improve their financial status. However, they end up in prison and their wives are forced to lead an independent life.

Data.title: Alex Cross (2012)
Data.desc: Detective and forensic psychologist Alex Cross is on his last mission to track down a homicidal killer, Picasso, who is known for torturing and killing rich businessmen in Detroit.

Data.title: The Exorcist (1973)
Data.desc: An actress notices dangerous changes in the behavior and physical make-up of her 12-year-old daughter. Meanwhile, a young priest begins to doubt his faith while dealing with his mother's sickness.

Data.title: XXX (2002)
Data.desc: The US government recruits extreme sports athlete Xander Cage to infiltrate a Russian criminal ring, which is plotting the destruction of the world.

Data.title: Survival Island (2005)
Data.desc: A boat blaze leaves rich girl Jennifer stranded on a desert island with only dishy deckhand Manuel for company. When her husband washes up a few days later, the situation takes a sinister turn.

Data.title: RoboCop (2014)
Data.desc: When Alex Murphy, a cop, gets injured in a bomb explosion, he is transformed into a robot police officer in order to combat criminal activities in the United States.

Data.title: John Wick (2014)
Data.desc: An ex-hit-man comes out of retirement to track down the gangsters that killed his dog and took everything from him.

Data.title: Johnny English Reborn (2011)
Data.desc: After a disastrous mission in Mozambique, British agent Johnny English (Rowan Atkinson) has retreated to a Tibetan monastery to try to forget his shame. But when he receives an urgent call from MI-7 to lead a mission that only he can handle, English is back in action. Using his questionable combat skills and an assortment of high-tech gadgets, English, along with his new partner, Agent Tucker (Daniel Kaluuya), must foil a plot to kill the Chinese premier.

Data.title: Psycho III (1986)
Data.desc: Norman Bates, the psychotic owner of 'Bates Motel', lived with the corpse of his mother. A stint of curiosity evolves, when people who had visited his motel went missing. Was he responsible for it?

Data.title: The Amazing Spider-Man (2012)
Data.desc: Peter Parker, an outcast high school student, gets bitten by a radioactive spider and attains superpowers. While unraveling his parents' disappearance, he must fight against the Lizard.

Data.title: The Darkest Hour (2011)
Data.desc: Five civilians turn heroes to save the people of Moscow city from an alien invasion. They soon learn that the invasion is worldwide and begin to discover a way to kill the aliens.

Data.title: American Pie Presents The Book of Love (2009)
Data.desc: Three new hapless virgins discover the legendary 'Book of Love', hidden in the school library. The ruined copy, with incomplete advice, leads them on a hilarious journey to lose their virginity.

Data.title: The Dirt (2019)
Data.desc: The misfits of M√∂tley Cr√ºe rise from the streets of Hollywood to the heights of international fame in the 1980s.

Data.title: Brotherhood Of Blades 2 (2017)
Data.desc: A general was forced to kill his partner in an operation and must try to avoid being found guilty while being blackmailed by a mysterious woman. Turns out there is a bigger scheme behind all this.

Data.title: The Dark Knight Rises (2012)
Data.desc: Bane, an imposing terrorist, attacks Gotham City and disrupts its eight-year-long period of peace. This forces Bruce Wayne to come out of hiding and don the cape and cowl of Batman again.

Data.title: Mr. Bean's Holiday (2007)
Data.desc: Mr. Bean wins a holiday to France and sets out on his journey. Once there, he unknowingly separates a father-son duo and then decides to reunite them.

Data.title: Apollo 13 (1995)
Data.desc: Astronauts Lovell, Haise and Swigert of the Apollo 13 moon mission find themselves stranded when their spacecraft gets damaged. NASA must now find a way to bring them back before it is too late.

Data.title: Bean (1997)
Data.desc: Mr Bean, a lazy security guard, is sent to the United States to bring a valued painting to a museum in Los Angeles. The mishaps in his journey lead to comical adventures.

Data.title: Cowboys And Aliens (2011)
Data.desc: Jake Lonergan enters the town of Absolution with no memory of how he turned up in the desert. However, he becomes the townspeople's only hope when aliens suddenly attack.

Data.title: American Reunion (2012)
Data.desc: A group of friends visit their hometown after a decade. While they reminisce over their school life and await the upcoming reunion, another high school senior is on the lookout for the perfect date.

Data.title: Jaws 3 (1983)
Data.desc: A group of marine biologists attempt to capture a young great white shark. Later, chaos follows when its ferocious mother breaks into the marine centre in order to avenge the death of its baby.

Data.title: Flash Point (2007)
Data.desc: An inspector risks the lives of an undercover police officer and his girlfriend as he tries to take on a small but powerful Vietnamese-Chinese gang which is wanted for murder.

Data.title: Riddick (2013)
Data.desc: Riddick finds himself on a sun-scorched planet and tries hard to fight for survival. He stands up against a race of alien predators, more lethal than any human race he has ever encountered.

Data.title: Goosebumps 2: Haunted Halloween (2018)
Data.desc: While collecting junk one day, best friends Sonny and Sam meet Slappy, a mischievous talking dummy from an unpublished "Goosebumps" book by R.L. Stine. Hoping to start his own family, Slappy kidnaps Sonny's mother and brings all of his ghoulish friends back to life -- just in time for Halloween. As the sleepy town becomes overrun with monsters, witches and other mysterious creatures, Sonny joins forces with his sister, Sam and a kindly neighbor to save Sonny's mom and foil Slappy's plan.

Data.title: Creed (2015)
Data.desc: Adonis Johnson, the son of heavyweight champion Apollo Creed, embraces his legacy as a boxer and seeks mentorship from Rocky Balboa, his father's old friend and rival.

Data.title: Legend Of The Demon Cat (2017)
Data.desc: A poet and a monk join forces to investigate the mysterious death of a concubine.

Data.title: Dawn of the Planet of the Apes (2014)
Data.desc: Ten years after a rife disease that significantly reduced the human population, apes who have endured the virus are drawn into a ferocious battle with a bunch of human survivors.

Data.title: American Pie Presents: Band Camp (2005)
Data.desc: Matt Stifler, Steve's younger brother, must attend band camp all summer after pulling a prank at high school. Things take a turn when he meets his childhood sweetheart, Elyse, at band camp.

Data.title: Lara Croft: Tomb Raider - The Cradle of Life (2003)
Data.desc: Lara Croft races against time to locate the legendary Pandora's box before it falls in the hands of the evil Jonathan Reiss, who plans to use the box to make weapons of mass destruction.

Data.title: Escape Room (2019)
Data.desc: Six adventurous strangers travel to a mysterious building to experience the escape room -- a game where players compete to solve a series of puzzles to win $10,000. What starts out as seemingly innocent fun soon turns into a living nightmare as the four men and two women discover each room is an elaborate trap that's part of a sadistic game of life or death.

Data.title: Time Raiders (2016)
Data.desc: A man follows clues in a notebook to track his missing uncle, a renowned archaeologist. Eventually, he tracks him to an ancient tomb that may hold the secrets of immortality.

Data.title: The Green Hornet (2011)
Data.desc: After his father's death, Britt inherits the largest media company in Los Angeles. He teams up with Kato to fight crime, but ends up becoming the target of an underworld don, Benjamin Chudnofsky.

Data.title: Bait (2012)
Data.desc: A freak tsunami traps shoppers at a coastal Australian supermarket inside the building. The shoppers have to deal with a deadly and unwanted visitor, which is a 12-foot Great White Shark.

Data.title: Piranha II: The Spawning (1981)
Data.desc: When a number of people are killed off the coast of a Caribbean island, Anne, a diving instructor, investigates and finds out that a shoal of mutant piranha is behind the attacks.

Data.title: Hercules (2014)
Data.desc: Hercules travels to Greece with his five loyal companions to sell his services for gold. A warlord threatens the king of Thrace to destroy his kingdom. Worried, the king approaches Hercules for help.

Data.title: The Great Wall (2016)
Data.desc: After William Garrin, a mercenary, is held captive in prison, he figures a way to defeat the monsters that attack the Great Wall and joins the warriors to protect the region.

Data.title: Amityville The Awakening (2017)
Data.desc: After Belle learns that her new house was a site for a mass murder in 1974 and her brother who is in a comatose state comes back to life, she gets suspicious and believes that he is possessed.

Data.title: Fifty Shades Darker (2017)
Data.desc: While Christian wrestles with his inner demons, Anastasia must confront the anger and envy of the women who came before her.

Data.title: Pitch Perfect (2012)
Data.desc: Beca, a freshman at Barden University, is cajoled into joining The Bellas, her school's all-girls singing group. Injecting some much needed energy into their repertoire, The Bellas take on their male rivals in a campus competition.

Data.title: Star Wars: The Last Jedi (2017)
Data.desc: Rey seeks to learn the ways of the Jedi under Luke Skywalker, its remaining member, to reinvigorate the Resistance's war against the First Order.

Data.title: Star Wars The Force Awakens (2015)
Data.desc: A new order threatens to destroy the New Republic. Finn, Rey and Poe, backed by the Resistance and the Republic, must find a way to stop them and find Luke, the last surviving Jedi.

Data.title: Final Destination 5 (2011)
Data.desc: A premonition helps Sam and his colleagues escape a fatal accident. 'Death', however, isn't quite ready to part with its victims and decides to come after them.

Data.title: The Final Destination (2009)
Data.desc: After a young man's premonition of a deadly race-car crash helps saves the lives of his peers, Death sets out to collect those who evaded their end.

Data.title: Final Destination 3 (2006)
Data.desc: A student's premonition of a deadly rollercoaster ride saves her life and a lucky few, but not from Death itself, which seeks out those who escaped their fate.

Data.title: Final Destination 2 (2003)
Data.desc: When Kimberly has a violent premonition of a highway pileup she blocks the freeway, keeping a few others meant to die, safe...Or are they? The survivors mysteriously start dying and it's up to Kimberly to stop it before she's next.

Data.title: Final Destination (2000)
Data.desc: Alex saves his school friends from death when he gets a premonition that their plane will crash. However, they all later begin to die one by one in horrifying ways.

Data.title: Deadpool 2 (2018)
Data.desc: Foul-mouthed mutant mercenary Wade Wilson (AKA. Deadpool), brings together a team of fellow mutant rogues to protect a young boy with supernatural abilities from the brutal, time-traveling cyborg, Cable.

Data.title: Logan (2017)
Data.desc: In a future where mutants are nearly extinct, an elderly and weary Logan leads a quiet life. But when Laura, a mutant child pursued by scientists, comes to him for help, he must get her to safety.

Data.title: X-Men: Apocalypse (2016)
Data.desc: In the 1980s the X-Men must defeat an ancient all-powerful mutant, En Sabah Nur, who intends to thrive through bringing destruction to the world.

Data.title: Deadpool (2016)
Data.desc: A wisecracking mercenary gets experimented on and becomes immortal but ugly, and sets out to track down the man who ruined his looks.

Data.title: X-Men: Days of Future Past (2014)
Data.desc: The X-Men send Wolverine to the past in a desperate effort to change history and prevent an event that results in doom for both humans and mutants.

Data.title: The Wolverine (2013)
Data.desc: Wolverine comes to Japan to meet an old friend whose life he saved years ago, and gets embroiled in a conspiracy involving yakuza and mutants.

Data.title: X-Men: First Class (2011)
Data.desc: In the 1960s, superpowered humans Charles Xavier and Erik Lensherr work together to find others like them, but Erik's vengeful pursuit of an ambitious mutant who ruined his life causes a schism to divide them.

Data.title: X-Men Origins: Wolverine (2009)
Data.desc: The early years of James Logan, featuring his rivalry with his brother Victor Creed, his service in the special forces team Weapon X, and his experimentation into the metal-lined mutant Wolverine.

Data.title: X-Men: The Last Stand (2006)
Data.desc: The human government develops a cure for mutations, and Jean Gray becomes a darker uncontrollable persona called the Phoenix who allies with Magneto, causing escalation into an all-out battle for the X-Men.

Data.title: X2: X-Men United (2003)
Data.desc: When anti-mutant Colonel William Stryker kidnaps Professor X and attacks his school, the X-Men must ally with their archenemy Magneto to stop him.

Data.title: X-Men (2000)
Data.desc: Two mutants find themselves torn between two conflicting groups that have starkly contrasting ideologies with regard to the development of the mutant kind.

Data.title: Hellboy (2019)
Data.desc: Based on the graphic novels by Mike Mignola, Hellboy, caught between the worlds of the supernatural and human, battles an ancient sorceress bent on revenge.

Data.title: Mercy (2014)
Data.desc: Two young boys move with their mother to care for their unwell grandmother, who stays at a creepy farmhouse. During this time, they suspect that a dark spirit has entered her body.

Data.title: Captain America: Civil War (2016)
Data.desc: Friction arises between superheroes when one group supports the government's decision to implement a law to control their powers while the other opposes it.
